50|$|Optical {{computing}} {{is to use}} photons {{rather than}} conventional electrons for computing. There {{are quite a few}} instances of <b>optical</b> <b>computers</b> and successful use of them. The conventional logic gates use semiconductors, which use electrons for transporting the signals. In case of <b>optical</b> <b>computers,</b> the photons in a light beam are used to do computation.|$|E
