50|$|There {{is active}} {{research}} to make computers {{out of many}} promising new types of technology, such as <b>optical</b> <b>computers,</b> DNA computers, neural computers, and quantum computers. Most computers are universal, {{and are able to}} calculate any computable function, and are limited only by their memory capacity and operating speed. However different designs of computers can give very different performance for particular problems; for example quantum computers can potentially break some modern encryption algorithms (by quantum factoring) very quickly.|$|E
